Given that the rate of change of volume is $10\sin (\pi t/10)$ cubic
centimetres per day, the total change in the volume between \emph{t=0}
and \emph{t=5}, in cubic centimetres, is

\begin{align*}
\int_{0}^{5}10\sin (\pi t/10)dt &= \left [10 \frac{-10}{\pi} \cos (\pi t/10) \right ]_{0}^{5} \\
&= \frac{-100}{\pi}\left (\cos(5 \pi/10)-\cos(0/10) \right ) \\
&= \frac{-100}{\pi}(0-1) \\
&= \color{blue} \frac{100}{\pi}\end{align*}
